  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Aware, BeanFactoryAware, BeanNameAware, DisposableBean, InitializingBean, ApplicationContextAware, ChannelInterceptorAware, ExecutorChannelInterceptorAware, QueueChannelOperations, ExpressionCapable, NamedComponent, ConfigurableMetricsAware<AbstractMessageChannelMetrics>, IntegrationManagement, IntegrationStatsManagement, MessageChannelMetrics, PollableChannelManagement, QueueChannelManagement, TrackableComponent, MessageChannel, PollableChannel

    public class RendezvousChannel
extends QueueChannel
    A zero-capacity version of QueueChannel that delegates to a SynchronousQueue internally. This accommodates "handoff" scenarios (i.e. blocking while waiting for another party to send or receive).
    Author:
    Mark Fisher
